{% doc %}
  Virtual Try-On — PDP call-to-action that opens an AI-powered garment try-on.

  This file is the SSR body only. The platform-generated wrapper supplies the
  outer container `<div>` (the visibility gate, the `data-spectrum-*`
  attributes). The body renders a server-side CTA button for LCP and a JSON
  data block; the modal flow is built client-side by the snippet's JS asset.

  @param {string} mutation_handle - Mutation handle for DOM scoping (infrastructure).
  @param {string} experience_handle - Experience handle for attribution (infrastructure).
  @param {object} variant - Resolved snippet-instance variant; merchant-edited
                            props live on `variant.content`.
  @param {object} mo - spectrum_snippet_instance metaobject drop.
  @param {object} entry - Resolved default slot entry from spectrum.fbt_<state>;
                          `entry.content.recommendations` is the array of
                          product handles offered as try-with companions.

  variant.content fields (presentation only):
    - button_text            {string}  CTA label
    - button_style           {string}  "primary" | "secondary" | "outline"
    - button_icon            {boolean} show the camera glyph before the label
    - daily_generation_limit {number}  per-shopper daily generation cap
    - consent_text           {string}  consent copy shown before photo upload — carries the biometric (face) data disclosure and the third-party AI processor; the engineering default needs legal sign-off before live biometric collection
    - disclaimer_text        {string}  AI-generated-image disclaimer copy (incl. that the shopper's exact facial features may not be reproduced)
    - show_branding          {boolean} show the Spectrum watermark on the result image (internal)

  @example
  {% render '_sai-snippet-o1uear1c',
    variant: variant,
    mo: mo,
    entry: entry,
    mutation_handle: 'mut-o1uear1cabcd1234',
    experience_handle: 'spring-fashion'
  %}
{% enddoc %}

{%- comment -%}
  PDP-only: every render path is gated on the Shopify `product` global. Off a
  PDP `product` is nil and this snippet emits nothing — the CTA, the JSON data
  block, and the asset `<script>` are all skipped. The fail-closed visibility
  gate on the wrapper means a no-op render collapses cleanly.

  JSON data block contract: every interpolated value is piped through `| json`.
  `| json` unicode-escapes `<`, `>`, and line separators, so merchant- and
  shopper-authored strings (product titles, options) cannot terminate the
  surrounding <script> element. Never `| escape` inside a JSON <script> block —
  HTML entities are not decoded inside <script> raw-text, which breaks the
  client-side JSON.parse.

  Nil-tolerant metafield reads: a nil metafield value piped through `| json`
  emits the literal `null`, so the data block is always valid JSON regardless
  of whether the FBT recommendations metafield or the saved customer photo
  exist. The JS treats `null` as "feature unavailable".
{%- endcomment -%}

{% stylesheet %}
/* Virtual Try-On (o1uear1c) */

.sai-o1uear1c {
  display: block;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  margin-block: var(--sai-size-4);
  font-family: var(--sai-font-body);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-body-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight);
  color: var(--sai-color-fg);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__button {
  position: relative;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
  box-sizing: border-box;
  inline-size: 100%;
  min-block-size: 3.5rem;
  padding: var(--sai-size-3) var(--sai-size-5);
  border: 1px solid transparent;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  /* Clip the moving sheen to the button's rounded box. The attract-ring is an
     outset box-shadow, which overflow does not clip, so the pulse still shows. */
  overflow: hidden;
  isolation: isolate;
  cursor: pointer;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-body);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-body-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  font-size: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.4;
  text-align: center;
  transition: opacity var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1), transform
    var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1), background-color var(--sai-duration-1)
    var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}

/* Style modifiers map onto theme color tokens — no hardcoded palette. */
.sai-o1uear1c__button--primary {
  background-color: var(--sai-color-primary);
  border-color: var(--sai-color-primary);
  color: var(--sai-color-primary-fg);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__button--secondary {
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  border-color: var(--sai-color-fg);
  color: var(--sai-color-fg);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__button--outline {
  background-color: transparent;
  border-color: var(--sai-color-fg);
  color: var(--sai-color-fg);
}

@media (hover: hover) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__button:hover {
    opacity: 0.88;
  }
}

.sai-o1uear1c__button:active {
  transform: scale(0.99);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__button:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__icon {
  display: inline-flex;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  inline-size: 1.125rem;
  block-size: 1.125rem;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__icon svg {
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
}

/* Expressive treatment for the filled primary CTA only: a periodic light sheen
   and an attract-ring pulse on first paint. Both are built from the theme's
   own --sai-color-primary (the sheen is a neutral white-alpha gradient; the
   ring is a primary-derived shadow via color-mix) so the button keeps the
   merchant's palette — no hardcoded accent. Outline/secondary stay calm. */
.sai-o1uear1c__shine {
  position: absolute;
  inset-block: 0;
  inline-size: 34%;
  inset-inline-start: 0;
  background: linear-gradient(
    100deg,
    transparent,
    rgb(255 255 255 / 0.42),
    transparent
  );
  pointer-events: none;
  z-index: 0;
  transform: translateX(-180%) skewX(-18deg);
  animation: sai-o1uear1c-shine 3.6s ease-in-out infinite;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__button--primary {
  animation: sai-o1uear1c-attract 2.4s var(--sai-ease-out-1) 3;
}

/* The label/icon sit above the sheen. */
.sai-o1uear1c__icon,
.sai-o1uear1c__label {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
}

@keyframes sai-o1uear1c-shine {
  0%,
  8% {
    transform: translateX(-180%) skewX(-18deg);
  }
  48%,
  100% {
    transform: translateX(320%) skewX(-18deg);
  }
}

@keyframes sai-o1uear1c-attract {
  0% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-primary) 45%, transparent);
  }
  70% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 12px color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-primary) 0%, transparent);
  }
  100% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-primary) 0%, transparent);
  }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__button {
    transition: none;
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__button--primary {
    animation: none;
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__shine {
    display: none;
  }
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   Modal — built and appended to <body> by the JS asset on first open.
   A native <dialog> is used so the modal escapes theme overflow/transform
   clipping (top layer), traps focus, closes on Esc, and gets ::backdrop for
   free. These rules live on <body>-level nodes, so they are intentionally
   not nested under .sai-o1uear1c — but every class still carries the
   sai-o1uear1c__ prefix, so the selectors stay snippet-scoped.
   ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

.sai-o1uear1c__dialog {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  /* Design role-colours mapped onto the merchant's theme tokens. The modal
     keeps the studio look on any storefront by deriving its ink/line/accent
     ramp from --sai-color-fg / --sai-color-primary rather than hardcoding a
     palette. */
  --o-ink: var(--sai-color-fg);
  --o-ink-2: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 68%, transparent);
  --o-ink-3: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 46%, transparent);
  --o-line: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 14%, transparent);
  --o-line-2: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 8%, transparent);
  --o-accent: var(--sai-color-primary);
  --o-accent-soft: color-mix(in srgb, var(--o-accent) 12%, var(--sai-color-bg));
  --o-on-stage: #ffffff;
  /* ONE locked footprint for the entire flow. Consent → photo → processing →
     result all share the same frame, so the modal never resizes as the shopper
     advances — only the content inside it changes. Sized in px (capped to the
     viewport) so it stays generously sized on themes that scale rem from a
     small root font-size. */
  inline-size: min(960px, calc(100vw - 24px));
  block-size: min(680px, calc(100dvh - 24px));
  margin: auto;
  padding: 0;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 20px;
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  color: var(--sai-color-fg);
  font-family: var(--sai-font-body);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-body-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight);
  overflow: hidden;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__dialog::backdrop {
  background-color: rgb(0 0 0 / 0.55);
}

/* Entrance: the frame rises and fades in as it opens. Native <dialog> applies
   [open] the moment showModal() runs, so the animation plays on first paint. */
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog[open] {
  animation: sai-o1uear1c-fade-up 0.25s var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}

@keyframes sai-o1uear1c-fade-up {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(8px);
  }
  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__dialog[open] {
    animation: none;
  }
}

/* Every element inside the modal uses border-box sizing so the snippet's
   px/rem paddings land predictably. The snippet sets the properties it cares
   about explicitly on its own scoped classes. */
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog *,
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog *::before,
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog *::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__shell {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  block-size: 100%;
}

/* Input steps (consent / colour / photo / processing) center their content
   inside the fixed-width modal so a short form doesn't stretch edge-to-edge.
   The header stays full-width (close pinned right). The two-pane looks result
   (--looks) and the full-bleed single-image result (--result) opt out — they
   fill the whole width. */
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog:not(.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--looks):not(.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--result)
  .sai-o1uear1c__body,
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog:not(.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--looks):not(.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--result)
  .sai-o1uear1c__footer {
  inline-size: 100%;
  max-inline-size: 34rem;
  margin-inline: auto;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: var(--sai-size-3);
  padding: var(--sai-size-4) var(--sai-size-5);
  border-block-end: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 12%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__title {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-heading);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-heading-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-heading-weight);
  font-size: 1.0625rem;
  line-height: 1.3;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__close {
  display: inline-flex;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  inline-size: 2rem;
  block-size: 2rem;
  padding: 0;
  border: none;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-round);
  background-color: transparent;
  color: currentColor;
  cursor: pointer;
}

@media (hover: hover) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__close:hover {
    background-color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 10%, transparent);
  }
}

.sai-o1uear1c__close:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__body {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  flex: 1 1 auto;
  min-block-size: 0;
  padding: var(--sai-size-5);
  overflow-y: auto;
  /* Full-width states (error / rate-limit) center their message instead of
     pinning it to the top. `safe` keeps tall content top-aligned + scrollable.
     The two-pane studio body (--looks) overrides this below. */
  justify-content: safe center;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__footer {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: var(--sai-size-3);
  padding: var(--sai-size-4) var(--sai-size-5);
  border-block-start: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 12%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__step-title {
  margin: 0 0 var(--sai-size-2);
  font-size: 1rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
}

/* Action buttons inside the modal — primary / ghost variants. */
.sai-o1uear1c__action {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
  min-block-size: 3.25rem;
  padding: var(--sai-size-2) var(--sai-size-5);
  border: 1px solid transparent;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  line-height: 1.3;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: opacity var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}

@media (hover: hover) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__action:not([disabled]):hover {
    opacity: 0.88;
  }
}

.sai-o1uear1c__action:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__action[disabled] {
  cursor: not-allowed;
  opacity: 0.5;
}

/* The `hidden` attribute must beat the `display` declaration in the base
   rule above. A bare `[hidden]` selector (0,1,0) only ties the
   `.sai-o1uear1c__action` class, and the later base rule wins the cascade —
   so the JS-toggled "Try Complete Look" button would stay visible with no
   FBT items selected. Qualifying the selector with the class lifts it to
   (0,2,0) so `hidden` reliably wins. */
.sai-o1uear1c__action[hidden] {
  display: none;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__action--primary {
  background-color: var(--sai-color-primary);
  border-color: var(--sai-color-primary);
  color: var(--sai-color-primary-fg);
  flex: 1 1 auto;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__action--ghost {
  background-color: transparent;
  border-color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 35%, transparent);
  color: currentColor;
}

/* Consent step — granular checkboxes. */
.sai-o1uear1c__consent-list {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--sai-size-3);
  margin: 0 0 var(--sai-size-4);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__check {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: var(--sai-size-3);
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  line-height: 1.5;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__dialog input[type="checkbox"],
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog input[type="checkbox"]:hover,
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog input[type="checkbox"]:checked,
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog input[type="checkbox"]:checked:hover {
  -webkit-appearance: checkbox;
  appearance: auto;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  inline-size: 1.125rem;
  block-size: 1.125rem;
  margin-block-start: 0.0625rem;
  accent-color: var(--sai-color-primary);
  background: none;
  border: none;
  box-shadow: none;
  outline: none;
  opacity: 1;
}

/* Photo step. */
/* The saved-photo step: a short instruction, a composed portrait preview frame
   (consistent 3:4 like the result hero so any uploaded aspect reads as an
   intentional preview, not a small floating image), then a centered delete. */
.sai-o1uear1c__photo-hint {
  margin: 0 0 var(--sai-size-4);
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  line-height: 1.5;
  text-align: center;
  color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 70%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__photo-frame {
  inline-size: 100%;
  max-inline-size: 14rem;
  aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
  margin: 0 auto var(--sai-size-3);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 8%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__photo-preview {
  display: block;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
  object-fit: contain;
}

/* Per-family display framing for the result/preview frames. The default crop is
   the garment 3/4 (full-length); jewellery reframes to a head-and-shoulders
   neckline and makeup to a square face crop, so a necklace or lip-shade try-on
   reads at a sensible crop instead of a full-length portrait. The hook is
   data-vto-family on the dialog, set by the runtime from the resolved try-on
   family; an absent or 'garment' value matches no rule here and leaves the 3/4
   default untouched. */
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog[data-vto-family='jewellery'] .sai-o1uear1c__photo-frame,
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog[data-vto-family='jewellery'] .sai-o1uear1c__fbt-thumb {
  aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__dialog[data-vto-family='makeup'] .sai-o1uear1c__photo-frame,
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog[data-vto-family='makeup'] .sai-o1uear1c__fbt-thumb {
  aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__dropzone {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
  padding: var(--sai-size-6) var(--sai-size-4);
  margin-block-end: var(--sai-size-4);
  border: 1px dashed color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 35%, transparent);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  text-align: center;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__dropzone-hint {
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  line-height: 1.5;
  color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 65%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__file-input {
  position: absolute;
  inline-size: 1px;
  block-size: 1px;
  padding: 0;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  white-space: nowrap;
  border: 0;
}

/* Processing step. */
.sai-o1uear1c__processing {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--sai-size-4);
  padding: var(--sai-size-7) var(--sai-size-4);
  text-align: center;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__processing .sai-spinner {
  --sai-spinner-size: 2.5rem;
  --sai-spinner-color: var(--sai-color-primary);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__processing-text {
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
}

/* Result step. */
.sai-o1uear1c__result-frame {
  position: relative;
  margin-block-end: var(--sai-size-4);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 8%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__result-image {
  display: block;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: auto;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__badge {
  position: absolute;
  inset-block-start: var(--sai-size-2);
  inset-inline-end: var(--sai-size-2);
  padding: var(--sai-size-1) var(--sai-size-2);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-sm);
  background-color: rgb(0 0 0 / 0.7);
  color: #ffffff;
  font-size: 0.6875rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__watermark {
  position: absolute;
  inset-block-end: var(--sai-size-2);
  inset-inline-start: var(--sai-size-2);
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  padding: var(--sai-size-1) var(--sai-size-2);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-sm);
  background-color: rgb(0 0 0 / 0.55);
  color: #ffffff;
  text-decoration: none;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__watermark-logo {
  display: block;
  block-size: 13px;
  inline-size: auto;
  fill: currentColor;
}

/* Two-pane result stage: badge sits top-left (the floating close owns
   top-right); watermark is a bare serif wordmark bottom-right. */
.sai-o1uear1c__stage--result .sai-o1uear1c__badge {
  inset-block-start: 12px;
  inset-inline: 12px auto;
  border-radius: 999px;
  background-color: rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5);
  backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__stage--result .sai-o1uear1c__watermark {
  inset-block-end: 11px;
  inset-inline: auto 13px;
  padding: 0;
  background-color: transparent;
  border-radius: 0;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-heading);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-heading-weight);
  font-size: 12px;
  letter-spacing: 0.28em;
  color: rgb(255 255 255 / 0.88);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__disclaimer {
  margin: 0 0 var(--sai-size-4);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  line-height: 1.5;
  color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 65%, transparent);
}

/* In-image loading — shown on the try-on image while a filmstrip look change or
   scene change regenerates, so the rest of the modal stays put. The result
   frame is position:relative, so this covers exactly the image. A subtle
   frosted base (::before) dims the previous result; the label pill reads
   "working" without a spinner. */
.sai-o1uear1c__result-loading {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  z-index: 3;
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-end;
  justify-content: center;
  padding-block-end: var(--sai-size-5);
  overflow: hidden;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__result-loading::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-bg) 32%, transparent);
  backdrop-filter: blur(1px);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__result-loading-text {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
  padding: var(--sai-size-2) var(--sai-size-4);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-round);
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-bg) 88%, transparent);
  color: var(--sai-color-fg);
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  letter-spacing: 0.01em;
}

/* Animated trailing dots on the label. */
.sai-o1uear1c__result-loading-text::after {
  content: '';
  animation: sai-o1uear1c-dots 1.4s steps(1) infinite;
}

@keyframes sai-o1uear1c-dots {
  0% { content: ''; }
  25% { content: '.'; }
  50% { content: '..'; }
  75% { content: '...'; }
  100% { content: ''; }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__result-loading-text::after {
    animation: none;
  }
}

/* Result step — full-bleed variant. The result is the only step that drops
   the header bar: the close floats over the image as a translucent disc and
   the generated image bleeds to the dialog edges. Scoped to the
   .sai-o1uear1c__dialog--result modifier (toggled by _setStep) so the
   consent / colour / photo steps keep their normal header. */
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--result .sai-o1uear1c__header {
  position: absolute;
  inset-block-start: 0;
  inset-inline: 0;
  z-index: 2;
  /* The title is hidden on this step, so the lone close must be pinned right
     rather than left (the base rule's space-between would send it left). */
  justify-content: flex-end;
  border-block-end: none;
  pointer-events: none;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--result .sai-o1uear1c__title {
  display: none;
}

/* Floating close — a translucent disc legible over any image. */
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--result .sai-o1uear1c__close {
  pointer-events: auto;
  background-color: rgb(0 0 0 / 0.45);
  color: #ffffff;
}

@media (hover: hover) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__dialog--result .sai-o1uear1c__close:hover {
    background-color: rgb(0 0 0 / 0.62);
  }
}

/* Image bleeds to the dialog edges; the dialog's own radius + overflow:hidden
   round the top corners. The pull-up cancels the body's top padding only when
   the frame is the first child — a transient notice, when present, keeps it. */
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--result .sai-o1uear1c__result-frame {
  margin-inline: calc(-1 * var(--sai-size-5));
  border-radius: 0;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--result .sai-o1uear1c__result-frame:first-child {
  margin-block-start: calc(-1 * var(--sai-size-5));
}

/* Keep the AI badge clear of the floating close (both sit top-right). */
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--result .sai-o1uear1c__badge {
  inset-inline: var(--sai-size-2) auto;
}

/* Result actions share one row evenly rather than wrapping to a stack. */
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--result .sai-o1uear1c__footer {
  flex-wrap: nowrap;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--result .sai-o1uear1c__footer .sai-o1uear1c__action {
  flex: 1 1 0;
  min-inline-size: 0;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__section-title {
  margin: var(--sai-size-5) 0 var(--sai-size-2);
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

/* Scene changer — horizontal thumbnail strip. */
.sai-o1uear1c__scene-strip {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0 0 var(--sai-size-1);
  list-style: none;
  overflow-x: auto;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__scene {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  gap: var(--sai-size-1);
  inline-size: 5rem;
  padding: 0;
  border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 22%, transparent);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  background-color: transparent;
  color: currentColor;
  font-family: inherit;
  cursor: pointer;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__scene[aria-pressed='true'] {
  border-color: var(--sai-color-primary);
  box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px var(--sai-color-primary);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__scene:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__scene[disabled] {
  cursor: not-allowed;
  opacity: 0.5;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__scene-thumb {
  aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
  inline-size: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 8%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__scene-name {
  padding: 0 var(--sai-size-1) var(--sai-size-1);
  font-size: 0.6875rem;
  line-height: 1.3;
  text-align: center;
}

/* FBT recommendations. */
.sai-o1uear1c__fbt-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(9rem, 1fr));
  gap: var(--sai-size-3);
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  list-style: none;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__fbt-card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
  padding: var(--sai-size-2);
  border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 18%, transparent);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__fbt-thumb {
  aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
  inline-size: 100%;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-sm);
  object-fit: cover;
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 8%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__fbt-name {
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  line-height: 1.35;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__fbt-price {
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 75%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__fbt-actions {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
  margin-block-start: auto;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__fbt-btn {
  flex: 1 1 0;
  min-block-size: 2.25rem;
  padding: var(--sai-size-1) var(--sai-size-2);
  border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 30%, transparent);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-sm);
  background-color: transparent;
  color: currentColor;
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  cursor: pointer;
}

@media (hover: hover) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__fbt-btn:hover {
    background-color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 8%, transparent);
  }
}

.sai-o1uear1c__fbt-btn:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 1px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__fbt-btn[aria-pressed='true'] {
  background-color: var(--sai-color-primary);
  border-color: var(--sai-color-primary);
  color: var(--sai-color-primary-fg);
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   Editorial-look filmstrip ("Tap to wear") + active look's product list.
   ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.sai-o1uear1c__looks-strip {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--sai-size-3);
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0 0 var(--sai-size-1);
  list-style: none;
  overflow-x: auto;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__look {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
  inline-size: 5.5rem;
  padding: 0;
  border: none;
  background: none;
  color: currentColor;
  font-family: inherit;
  text-align: center;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__look[disabled] {
  cursor: not-allowed;
  opacity: 0.55;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__look-thumb-wrap {
  position: relative;
  aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
  inline-size: 100%;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  border: 2px solid transparent;
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 8%, transparent);
  overflow: hidden;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__look[aria-pressed='true'] .sai-o1uear1c__look-thumb-wrap {
  border-color: var(--sai-color-primary);
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--sai-color-primary);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__look-thumb {
  display: block;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}

/* When a look has no styled hero image, the tile is a collage of the look's
   actual product images — so the tile always matches the items in the look. */
.sai-o1uear1c__look-collage {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  grid-auto-rows: 1fr;
  gap: 1px;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__look-collage-img {
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}

/* An odd last image spans both columns so the grid never leaves a gap. */
.sai-o1uear1c__look-collage-img:last-child:nth-child(odd) {
  grid-column: 1 / -1;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__look-count {
  position: absolute;
  inset-block-end: var(--sai-size-1);
  inset-inline-end: var(--sai-size-1);
  min-inline-size: 1.125rem;
  padding: 0 0.25rem;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-round);
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  color: var(--sai-color-fg);
  font-size: 0.6875rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  line-height: 1.4;
  text-align: center;
  box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.2);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__look-name {
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  line-height: 1.3;
  color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 70%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__look[aria-pressed='true'] .sai-o1uear1c__look-name {
  color: currentColor;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
}

/* Active look's product list — header (eyebrow + heading + piece count) then a
   row per product with a size picker + add. */
.sai-o1uear1c__look-head {
  margin-block-end: var(--sai-size-3);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__look-eyebrow {
  font-size: 0.6875rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 50%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__look-heading {
  margin-block-start: 0.125rem;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-heading);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-heading-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-heading-weight);
  font-size: 1.375rem;
  line-height: 1.15;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__look-meta {
  margin-block-start: 0.25rem;
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 58%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-list {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  list-style: none;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 13px;
  padding: 14px 0;
  border-block-start: 1px solid var(--o-line-2);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-list .sai-o1uear1c__lookrow:first-child {
  border-block-start: none;
  padding-block-start: 0;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-thumb {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  inline-size: 54px;
  block-size: 66px;
  border-radius: 9px;
  object-fit: cover;
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 8%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-info {
  flex: 1 1 auto;
  min-inline-size: 0;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-role {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--o-ink-3);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-name {
  margin-block-start: 2px;
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  line-height: 1.3;
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-price {
  margin-block-start: 2px;
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--o-ink-2);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-controls {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 8px;
  flex: none;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-variant {
  min-block-size: 38px;
  padding: 0 12px;
  border: 1px solid var(--o-line);
  border-radius: 9px;
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  color: var(--o-ink);
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 500;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-variant:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 1px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-add {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  min-block-size: 38px;
  padding: 0 16px;
  /* Match the adjacent variant-select's hairline (--o-line) rather than a full
     --o-ink border, which reads as a heavy near-black box on dark-ink themes. */
  border: 1px solid var(--o-line);
  border-radius: 9px;
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  color: var(--o-ink);
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 13px;
  /* Match the adjacent variant select's weight (500); bold (700) made the
     "Add" read heavier/darker than the rest of the row's controls. */
  font-weight: 500;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background-color 0.18s ease, color 0.18s ease;
}

@media (hover: hover) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-add:not([disabled]):hover {
    background-color: var(--o-ink);
    color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  }
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-add[disabled] {
  cursor: not-allowed;
  opacity: 0.45;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-add:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 1px;
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   Two-pane editorial-look result lightbox. Left (stage): the try-on image +
   the "Tap to wear" filmstrip. Right (panel): the worn look's products + the
   add-to-bag action. Stacks to a single column on narrow viewports.
   ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
/* The two-pane layout supplies its own close (in the panel head) + add (in the
   panel foot), so the shared shell header/footer are hidden. */
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--looks .sai-o1uear1c__header,
.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--looks .sai-o1uear1c__footer {
  display: none;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__dialog--looks .sai-o1uear1c__body {
  display: flex;
  min-block-size: 0;
  padding: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__lightbox {
  position: relative;
  display: flex;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
  min-block-size: 0;
}

/* Left pane ("stage"). Consent/photo/processing fill it edge-to-edge with a
   single visual; the result turns it into a padded column (hero + filmstrip).
   Fixed width so the flexible panel carries the richer controls. */
.sai-o1uear1c__stage {
  position: relative;
  flex: none;
  inline-size: 420px;
  min-inline-size: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: var(--o-accent-soft);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__stage--result {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  padding: 18px;
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 6%, var(--sai-color-bg));
}

/* Result hero fills the padded stage above the filmstrip (object-fit cover
   keeps any aspect from distorting). */
.sai-o1uear1c__stage--result .sai-o1uear1c__result-frame {
  flex: 1 1 auto;
  min-block-size: 0;
  inline-size: 100%;
  margin: 0;
  border-radius: 14px;
  overflow: hidden;
  box-shadow: 0 6px 16px -14px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.35);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__stage--result .sai-o1uear1c__result-image {
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}

/* Makeup before/after — the shopper's own photo beside the generated result so
   the lip-shade change is easy to judge. A static side-by-side (no slider or
   toggle) is the robust default: no interaction state, and each half cover-crops
   to the same frame the makeup family already faces. The frame's AI badge sits
   top-start and the watermark bottom-end, so the pane labels sit bottom-centre to
   stay clear of both. */
.sai-o1uear1c__ba {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__ba-pane {
  position: relative;
  margin: 0;
  min-inline-size: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
}

/* Hairline seam so the two halves read as a deliberate comparison. */
.sai-o1uear1c__ba-pane + .sai-o1uear1c__ba-pane {
  border-inline-start: 1px solid rgb(255 255 255 / 0.5);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__ba-img {
  display: block;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__ba-label {
  position: absolute;
  inset-block-end: 10px;
  inset-inline: 0;
  margin-inline: auto;
  inline-size: fit-content;
  padding: 3px 10px;
  border-radius: 999px;
  background-color: rgb(0 0 0 / 0.55);
  backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
  color: #ffffff;
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

/* Full-bleed stage visual for consent / photo / processing. */
.sai-o1uear1c__stage-card {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: var(--o-accent-soft);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__stage-img {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  display: block;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}

/* Aspirational/empty placeholder fill when no styled image is available. */
.sai-o1uear1c__stage-card--placeholder {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background-image: linear-gradient(
    160deg,
    color-mix(in srgb, var(--o-accent) 30%, var(--sai-color-bg)),
    color-mix(in srgb, var(--o-accent) 10%, var(--sai-color-bg))
  );
  color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--o-accent) 55%, transparent);
}

/* Italic editorial caption along the bottom of a stage visual. */
.sai-o1uear1c__stage-cap {
  position: absolute;
  inset-inline: 0;
  inset-block-end: 0;
  padding: 48px 26px 26px;
  background-image: linear-gradient(to top, rgb(0 0 0 / 0.62), transparent);
  color: var(--o-on-stage);
  font-family: var(--sai-font-heading);
  font-style: italic;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-heading-weight);
  font-size: 26px;
  line-height: 1.2;
  max-inline-size: 13ch;
}

/* Processing — the shopper's photo dimmed under a soft "developing" pulse, so it
   reads as the AI working on THEIR image. */
.sai-o1uear1c__stage-img--dim {
  filter: brightness(0.62) saturate(0.85);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__scan {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  pointer-events: none;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__scan::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--o-accent) 10%, transparent);
  mix-blend-mode: screen;
  animation: sai-o1uear1c-develop 3.4s ease-in-out infinite alternate;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__scan-label {
  position: absolute;
  inset-inline: 0;
  inset-block-end: 0;
  padding: 22px;
  background-image: linear-gradient(0deg, rgb(0 0 0 / 0.55), transparent);
  color: var(--o-on-stage);
  font-size: 11px;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 7px;
}

@keyframes sai-o1uear1c-develop {
  0% {
    clip-path: inset(0 0 100% 0);
  }
  100% {
    clip-path: inset(0 0 0 0);
  }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__scan::after {
    animation: none;
  }
}

/* Calm, deliberate generation status in the panel — a single advancing line
   with a pulsing dot. Replaces a big spinner + jumpy centered messages, which
   read as placeholder rather than product. */
.sai-o1uear1c__gen-status {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
  margin: 0 0 var(--sai-size-3);
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  line-height: 1.3;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__gen-dot {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  inline-size: 0.5rem;
  block-size: 0.5rem;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-round);
  background-color: var(--sai-color-primary);
  animation: sai-o1uear1c-pulse 1.2s ease-in-out infinite;
}

@keyframes sai-o1uear1c-pulse {
  0%, 100% {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: scale(1);
  }
  50% {
    opacity: 0.35;
    transform: scale(0.65);
  }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__gen-dot {
    animation: none;
  }
}

/* Right pane ("panel") — the flexible controls column. */
.sai-o1uear1c__panel {
  display: flex;
  flex: 1 1 auto;
  flex-direction: column;
  min-inline-size: 0;
  min-block-size: 0;
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  /* Subtle seam between the stage and the controls. Desktop only — the mobile
     query stacks the panes and clears this (a stacked left border reads as a
     stray vertical line). */
  border-inline-start: 1px solid var(--o-line);
}

/* Step-dots header (consent / photo / processing). */
.sai-o1uear1c__panel-head {
  display: flex;
  flex: 0 0 auto;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 7px;
  padding: 26px 30px 0;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__step-dot {
  inline-size: 7px;
  block-size: 7px;
  border-radius: 999px;
  background-color: var(--o-line);
  transition: inline-size 0.3s ease, background-color 0.3s ease;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__step-dot--done {
  background-color: var(--o-accent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__step-dot--active {
  inline-size: 20px;
  background-color: var(--o-accent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__step-label {
  margin-inline-start: 6px;
  font-size: 11px;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--o-ink-3);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__panel-body {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  flex: 1 1 auto;
  min-block-size: 0;
  padding: 18px 22px 22px;
  overflow-y: auto;
  /* Short steps (uploading, photo-ready, processing) center in the tall fixed
     frame so they don't strand at the top over a void. `safe` falls back to
     top-aligned when content is taller than the panel (consent), so nothing
     gets clipped above the scroll. */
  justify-content: safe center;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__panel-body--result {
  padding-block-start: 28px;
  /* The result panel has real content (eyebrow, name, product list); keep it
     top-aligned. Only the sparse input steps use the centering on the base
     .sai-o1uear1c__panel-body rule. */
  justify-content: flex-start;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__panel-foot {
  display: flex;
  flex: 0 0 auto;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 10px;
  padding: 16px 22px;
  /* Same hairline as the stage/panel divider so the modal's separators read
     as one system. */
  border-block-start: 1px solid var(--o-line);
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__panel-foot--row {
  flex-direction: row;
  gap: 11px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__panel-foot .sai-o1uear1c__action {
  inline-size: 100%;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__panel-foot--row .sai-o1uear1c__action {
  inline-size: auto;
}

/* Floating circular close — one control over the whole frame, every step. */
.sai-o1uear1c__float-close {
  position: absolute;
  inset-block-start: 16px;
  inset-inline-end: 16px;
  z-index: 20;
  inline-size: 36px;
  block-size: 36px;
  padding: 0;
  border-radius: 50%;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  border: 1px solid var(--o-line);
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-bg) 90%, transparent);
  color: var(--o-ink);
  cursor: pointer;
  backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
}

@media (hover: hover) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__float-close:hover {
    background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  }
}

.sai-o1uear1c__float-close:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* Panel headings + lede shared by the input steps. */
.sai-o1uear1c__panel-h2 {
  margin: 0 0 12px;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-heading);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-heading-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-heading-weight);
  font-size: 28px;
  line-height: 1.1;
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__panel-lede {
  margin: 0 0 22px;
  font-size: 14px;
  line-height: 1.65;
  color: var(--o-ink-2);
  max-inline-size: 42ch;
}

/* Consent — bordered selectable cards. */
.sai-o1uear1c__consent {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 10px;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  list-style: none;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__consent-row {
  display: flex;
  gap: 13px;
  align-items: flex-start;
  text-align: start;
  inline-size: 100%;
  padding: 14px 15px;
  border-radius: 12px;
  border: 1px solid var(--o-line);
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  color: var(--o-ink);
  font-family: inherit;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: border-color 0.18s ease, background-color 0.18s ease;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__consent-row[aria-pressed='true'] {
  border-color: var(--o-accent);
  background-color: var(--o-accent-soft);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__consent-row:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__consent-box {
  flex: none;
  inline-size: 22px;
  block-size: 22px;
  margin-block-start: 1px;
  border-radius: 7px;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  border: 1.5px solid var(--o-line);
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  color: var(--sai-color-primary-fg);
  transition: border-color 0.18s ease, background-color 0.18s ease;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__consent-row[aria-pressed='true'] .sai-o1uear1c__consent-box {
  border-color: var(--o-accent);
  background-color: var(--o-accent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__consent-title {
  display: block;
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  color: var(--o-ink);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__consent-desc {
  display: block;
  font-size: 12.5px;
  color: var(--o-ink-3);
  margin-block-start: 2px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__reassure {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: 6px;
  font-size: 11.5px;
  color: var(--o-ink-3);
  text-align: center;
}

/* Processing panel — progress bar + status stepper. */
.sai-o1uear1c__proc-status {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 12px;
  margin: 0 0 22px;
  font-size: 16px;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--o-ink);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__proc-bar {
  block-size: 6px;
  margin-block: 4px 0;
  border-radius: 999px;
  /* A soft tint of the theme accent so the track reads as a progress rail, not
     a hairline divider. */
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--o-accent) 16%, var(--sai-color-bg));
  overflow: hidden;
}

/* Scoped under the bar (specificity 0,2,0) so it outranks themes whose base
   CSS hides empty elements — e.g. Dawn/Horizon `div:empty { display:none }`
   at (0,1,1). The fill is an intentionally-empty styled div; without this the
   theme blanks it and the bar never appears to move. */
.sai-o1uear1c__proc-bar .sai-o1uear1c__proc-fill {
  display: block;
  block-size: 100%;
  inline-size: 0;
  border-radius: 999px;
  /* Solid accent fill (not a fade) so the filled portion stays high-contrast
     against the light track on monochrome themes, where a gradient to a lighter
     tint washes into the track and the bar reads as static. */
  background-color: var(--o-accent);
  transition: inline-size 0.25s linear;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__proc-steps {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 11px;
  margin-block-start: 24px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__proc-step {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 10px;
  font-size: 13.5px;
  color: var(--o-ink-3);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__proc-step--active {
  color: var(--o-ink);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__proc-step--done {
  color: var(--o-ink);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__proc-step-dot {
  flex: none;
  inline-size: 7px;
  block-size: 7px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background-color: var(--o-line);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__proc-step--active .sai-o1uear1c__proc-step-dot {
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--o-accent) 65%, white);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__proc-step--done .sai-o1uear1c__proc-step-dot {
  background-color: var(--o-accent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__proc-foot {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 7px;
  font-size: 12.5px;
  color: var(--o-ink-3);
}

/* Result panel — eyebrow + name row + solo hint + custom size select. */
.sai-o1uear1c__result-eyebrow {
  font-size: 11px;
  letter-spacing: 0.16em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--o-accent);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  margin-block-end: 6px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__result-headrow {
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: 10px;
  /* Clear the floating close (top-right of the frame) so the piece count never
     sits under it. */
  padding-inline-end: 40px;
  margin-block-end: 20px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__result-name {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-heading);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-heading-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-heading-weight);
  font-size: 26px;
  line-height: 1.1;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__result-pieces {
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--o-ink-3);
  white-space: nowrap;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__solo-hint {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: 11px;
  font-size: 12.5px;
  color: var(--o-ink-2);
  background-color: var(--o-accent-soft);
  padding: 12px 14px;
  border-radius: 11px;
  margin-block-end: 18px;
}

/* Custom select with chevron, used for the per-product size picker. */
.sai-o1uear1c__select-wrap {
  position: relative;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__select-wrap .sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-variant {
  appearance: none;
  -webkit-appearance: none;
  padding-inline-end: 28px;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__select-chevron {
  position: absolute;
  inset-inline-end: 9px;
  pointer-events: none;
  color: var(--o-ink-3);
}

/* Photo step — dropzone + ready chip (override the legacy token-based rules
   above with the studio's px treatment). */
.sai-o1uear1c__dropzone {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 12px;
  padding: 30px 22px;
  margin: 0;
  border: 1.5px dashed var(--o-line);
  border-radius: 14px;
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 3%, var(--sai-color-bg));
  text-align: center;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: border-color 0.18s ease, background-color 0.18s ease;
}

@media (hover: hover) {
  /* The resting icon tile and the dropzone's hover wash both derive from
     --o-accent-soft. Hovering to that exact wash makes the icon tile dissolve
     into the background. Keep the hover wash lighter than the tile, and deepen
     the tile on hover, so the two stay distinct. */
  .sai-o1uear1c__dropzone:hover {
    border-color: var(--o-accent);
    background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--o-accent) 5%, var(--sai-color-bg));
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__dropzone:hover .sai-o1uear1c__dropzone-icon {
    background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--o-accent) 18%, var(--sai-color-bg));
  }
}

.sai-o1uear1c__dropzone-icon {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  inline-size: 46px;
  block-size: 46px;
  border-radius: 12px;
  background-color: var(--o-accent-soft);
  color: var(--o-accent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__dropzone-hint {
  font-size: 13.5px;
  line-height: 1.5;
  color: var(--o-ink-2);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__ready-chip {
  display: inline-flex;
  /* The panel is a centering flex column; keep the chip hugging its label
     instead of stretching across the full panel width. */
  align-self: flex-start;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 8px;
  font-size: 12.5px;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  color: var(--sai-color-success, #2e7d4f);
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-success, #2e7d4f) 14%, var(--sai-color-bg));
  padding: 8px 12px;
  border-radius: 9px;
}

@media (max-width: 48rem) {
  /* Full-screen edge-to-edge sheet on phones. `margin: 0` removes the base rule's
     centered gutter; `100%` (not 100vw) fills the viewport without a scrollbar
     sliver in a preview iframe. */
  .sai-o1uear1c__dialog {
    inline-size: 100%;
    max-inline-size: none;
    block-size: 100dvh;
    max-block-size: none;
    margin: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__body {
    overflow-y: auto;
  }
  /* Single scroll on phones + tablets: the whole two-pane sheet (stage visual +
     panel controls) scrolls as ONE column. The desktop --looks body is a
     clipped flex row that hands the scroll to an inner panel, which trapped the
     product list in a short, separately-scrolling pane. Making the sheet body a
     plain block scroll container and letting the lightbox grow past the viewport
     moves the scroll to the sheet itself. */
  .sai-o1uear1c__dialog--looks .sai-o1uear1c__body {
    display: block;
    overflow-y: auto;
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__lightbox {
    flex-direction: column;
    min-block-size: 100%;
    block-size: auto;
  }
  /* Drop the inner panel scroll — panel content flows into the sheet's single
     scroll instead of nesting its own scrollbar. */
  .sai-o1uear1c__panel-body {
    overflow: visible;
  }
  /* Stage becomes a banner across the top; result gives it a touch more height
     for the hero + filmstrip. */
  .sai-o1uear1c__stage {
    inline-size: 100%;
    flex: none;
    block-size: 42vh;
  }
  /* Result stage sizes to its content now that the sheet scrolls as one: a
     prominent portrait hero (the generated try-on) with the "Tap to wear"
     filmstrip flowing beneath it, instead of both being crammed into a fixed
     52vh band that shrank the image to a letterbox. */
  .sai-o1uear1c__stage--result {
    block-size: auto;
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__stage--result .sai-o1uear1c__result-frame {
    flex: none;
    aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
    /* Portrait at phone widths (≈4:3 tall); capped so the wider tablet end of
       this breakpoint doesn't blow the hero up to near-full-screen. */
    max-block-size: 62vh;
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__panel {
    flex: 1 1 auto;
    border-inline-start: none;
  }
  /* Equal-width footer buttons on phones/tablets. The base primary action
     flex-grows (1 1 auto) so it otherwise renders wider than the ghost beside
     it; a zero flex-basis on both makes the row split evenly. */
  .sai-o1uear1c__panel-foot--row .sai-o1uear1c__action {
    flex: 1 1 0;
  }
  /* Only the result's add-to-bag CTA pins to the bottom while the sheet scrolls;
     the input-step footers (consent / photo / processing) share the
     .sai-o1uear1c__panel-foot class, so the result is singled out via its
     sibling result panel-body. The safe-area inset keeps the pinned bar clear of
     the home indicator on notched phones; the base rule supplies the background
     + top hairline so scrolling content doesn't bleed through. */
  .sai-o1uear1c__panel-body--result ~ .sai-o1uear1c__panel-foot {
    position: sticky;
    inset-block-end: 0;
    padding-block-end: calc(16px + env(safe-area-inset-bottom));
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__float-close {
    inset-block-start: calc(16px + env(safe-area-inset-top));
    inset-inline-end: calc(16px + env(safe-area-inset-right));
  }
  /* Phone summary row: thumbnail + name/price with Add pinned right on line 1;
     the size-select drops to line 2 under the name so the centre info keeps the
     row width. `display: contents` promotes the select + Add out of their
     wrapper so both can be placed directly in this grid. */
  .sai-o1uear1c__lookrow {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto;
    grid-template-areas:
      'thumb info   add'
      '.     select select';
    column-gap: 13px;
    row-gap: 8px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-thumb {
    grid-area: thumb;
    align-self: start;
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-info {
    grid-area: info;
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-controls {
    display: contents;
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-controls .sai-o1uear1c__select-wrap {
    grid-area: select;
    justify-self: start;
  }
  .sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-controls .sai-o1uear1c__lookrow-add {
    grid-area: add;
  }
}

/* Inline notices — errors, warnings, rate-limit messages. */
.sai-o1uear1c__notice {
  margin: 0 0 var(--sai-size-4);
  padding: var(--sai-size-3);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  line-height: 1.5;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__notice--warning {
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 8%, transparent);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__notice--error {
  background-color: var(--sai-color-error);
  color: var(--sai-color-error-fg);
}

.sai-o1uear1c__error-state {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--sai-size-3);
  padding: var(--sai-size-6) var(--sai-size-4);
  text-align: center;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__delete-link {
  display: block;
  margin: var(--sai-size-2) auto 0;
  padding: var(--sai-size-1);
  border: none;
  background: none;
  color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 70%, transparent);
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-underline-offset: 2px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.sai-o1uear1c__delete-link:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-o1uear1c__action {
    transition: none;
  }
}
{% endstylesheet %}

{%- if product -%}

  <script src="{{ 'sai-snippet-o1uear1c.js' | asset_url }}" async></script>

  {%- assign content = variant.content -%}
  {%- assign button_text = content.button_text | default: 'Try On With AI' -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    button_style is constrained to the three documented values; an unexpected
    or missing value falls back to 'outline' (the production-safe neutral that
    blends with any theme).
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- assign button_style = content.button_style -%}
  {%- if button_style != 'primary' and button_style != 'secondary' and button_style != 'outline' -%}
    {%- assign button_style = 'outline' -%}
  {%- endif -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    button_icon defaults to true. Liquid's `| default:` filter would replace an
    explicit `false`, so use an explicit nil check.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- if content.button_icon == nil -%}
    {%- assign button_icon = true -%}
  {%- else -%}
    {%- assign button_icon = content.button_icon -%}
  {%- endif -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    show_branding defaults to true (same boolean-nil-check reason as button_icon).
    Forwarded into the JSON payload; the client gates the result-image watermark.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- if content.show_branding == nil -%}
    {%- assign show_branding = true -%}
  {%- else -%}
    {%- assign show_branding = content.show_branding -%}
  {%- endif -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    Editorial-look companions for the "Complete the look" try-on, read from the
    same editorial-looks metafield the Shop the Look section consumes so VTO
    composites the curated outfit a merchant actually built (not generic FBT
    co-purchase recs). Resolved here off the `product` global rather than via
    the resource-slot wrapper: VTO is metaobject-backed, and a resource `source`
    would gate the CTA on a virtual_try_on slot metafield nothing provisions
    (see the snippet's template-invariants test).

    Draft/live coalesce: prefer `editorial_looks_draft` when present, else
    `editorial_looks_live`. Editorial looks promote straight to the live key
    today (no separate draft content), so this reads live in practice; if a
    draft is ever written it is preferred automatically. The deep walk
    (slots -> looks -> outfit -> products) is bounded and deduped below to stay
    within Shopify's connected-reference budget.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- assign sai_eli_slots = product.metafields.spectrum.editorial_looks_draft.value -%}
  {%- unless sai_eli_slots -%}
    {%- assign sai_eli_slots = product.metafields.spectrum.editorial_looks_live.value -%}
  {%- endunless -%}
  {%- assign sai_eli_current = product.id | append: '' -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    Try-on family (garment | jewellery | makeup), server-resolved per product
    from the spectrum.vto_family metafield (set white-glove alongside the
    per-product render config). Drives the snippet's per-family photo guidance
    and result display crop. Absent or blank falls back to garment, the
    production-safe default — a product with no family metafield keeps the
    unchanged garment flow. The client re-validates via resolveFamily, so an
    unexpected value still degrades to garment rather than reaching a strategy
    that cannot render it.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- assign vto_family = product.metafields.spectrum.vto_family.value -%}
  {%- if vto_family == blank -%}
    {%- assign vto_family = 'garment' -%}
  {%- endif -%}

  <sai-o1uear1c
    class="sai-o1uear1c"
    data-product-id="{{ product.id }}"
    data-product-handle="{{ product.handle }}"
    data-proxy-base="/apps/spectrum"
  >
    <button
      type="button"
      class="sai-o1uear1c__button sai-o1uear1c__button--{{ button_style }}"
      data-action="open-try-on"
    >
      {%- comment -%}
        The moving sheen is decorative and only rides the filled primary
        treatment, where it reads as intended; outline/secondary stay calm.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- if button_style == 'primary' -%}
        <span class="sai-o1uear1c__shine" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      {%- endif -%}
      {%- if button_icon -%}
        <span class="sai-o1uear1c__icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" focusable="false">
            <path d="M2 5.5C2 4.67157 2.67157 4 3.5 4H5L6 2.5H12L13 4H14.5C15.3284 4 16 4.67157 16 5.5V13C16 13.8284 15.3284 14.5 14.5 14.5H3.5C2.67157 14.5 2 13.8284 2 13V5.5Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <circle cx="9" cy="9" r="2.75" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          </svg>
        </span>
      {%- endif -%}
      <span class="sai-o1uear1c__label">{{ button_text }}</span>
    </button>

    {%- comment -%}
      Data block consumed once on init by the snippet JS. Per-value `| json` is
      mandatory (see the contract note in the leading comment). The shapes:
        - product : id, title, options[], available, plus variants[] each
                    carrying id / title / options[] / available / image URLs.
        - fbt     : raw value of product.metafields.spectrum.recommendations_fbt_live
                    (JSON authored by data ingestion) or null when absent.
        - editorialLooks : the current product's editorial-look outfit
                    companions (excluding the product itself) — one entry per
                    outfit product with its garment image + first-available
                    variant. The client prefers these over `fbt` for the
                    "Complete the look" try-on; an empty array falls back to fbt.
        - customerPhoto : raw value of the saved customer photo metafield, or
                          null for anonymous shoppers / shoppers with no photo.
        - vtoReferenceImage : raw value of product.metafields.spectrum.vto_reference_image
                              (a model-worn fit reference URL) or null. When
                              present the JS forwards it to /vto/generate as
                              `modelWornImageUrl`; generation works without it.
        - family  : the server-resolved try-on family (garment | jewellery |
                    makeup) from product.metafields.spectrum.vto_family, defaulted
                    to garment. Selects the single-product flow (no looks/scene/
                    complete-the-look) and the result display for the new families.
        - props   : the merchant-configurable presentation settings the modal
                    needs at runtime.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <script type="application/json" data-vto-payload>
{
  "product": {
    "id": {{ product.id | json }},
    "title": {{ product.title | json }},
    "handle": {{ product.handle | json }},
    {%- comment -%}
      Garment body region (top / bottom / whole-body) is resolved server-side
      from these so a single-garment try-on keeps the shopper's other clothing
      without a vision call. `type` is the merchant's free-text product type;
      `category` is the Shopify Standard Product Taxonomy name when set (nil-safe).
    {%- endcomment -%}
    "type": {{ product.type | json }},
    "category": {%- if product.category -%}{{ product.category.name | json }}{%- else -%}null{%- endif -%},
    "url": {{ product.url | json }},
    "options": {{ product.options | json }},
    "available": {{ product.available | json }},
    "featuredImageUrl": {%- if product.featured_image -%}{{ product.featured_image | image_url: width: 800 | json }}{%- else -%}null{%- endif -%},
    {%- comment -%} Money-formatted price for the current product's result row, mirroring look products. {%- endcomment -%}
    "price": {%- if product.selected_or_first_available_variant -%}{{ product.selected_or_first_available_variant.price | money | json }}{%- else -%}null{%- endif -%},
    "variants": [
      {%- for v in product.variants -%}
        {%- unless forloop.first -%},{%- endunless -%}
        {
          "id": {{ v.id | json }},
          "title": {{ v.title | json }},
          "options": {{ v.options | json }},
          "available": {{ v.available | json }},
          "imageUrl": {%- if v.image -%}{{ v.image | image_url: width: 800 | json }}{%- else -%}null{%- endif -%}
        }
      {%- endfor -%}
    ]
  },
  "fbt": {{ product.metafields.spectrum.recommendations_fbt_live.value | json }},
  "editorialLooks": [
    {%- assign sai_eli_seen = '|' -%}
    {%- assign sai_eli_count = 0 -%}
    {%- assign sai_eli_first = true -%}
    {%- if sai_eli_slots -%}
      {%- for sai_slot in sai_eli_slots -%}
        {%- if sai_eli_count >= 8 -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
        {%- if sai_slot.looks.value -%}
          {%- for sai_look in sai_slot.looks.value -%}
            {%- if sai_eli_count >= 8 -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
            {%- if sai_look.outfit.value -%}
              {%- for sai_oe in sai_look.outfit.value -%}
                {%- if sai_eli_count >= 8 -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
                {%- assign sai_eli_product = sai_oe.product.value -%}
                {%- if sai_eli_product -%}
                  {%- assign sai_eli_pid = sai_eli_product.id | append: '' -%}
                  {%- assign sai_eli_tok = '|' | append: sai_eli_pid | append: '|' -%}
                  {%- unless sai_eli_pid == sai_eli_current or sai_eli_seen contains sai_eli_tok -%}
                    {%- assign sai_eli_seen = sai_eli_seen | append: sai_eli_pid | append: '|' -%}
                    {%- assign sai_eli_count = sai_eli_count | plus: 1 -%}
                    {%- assign sai_eli_variant = sai_eli_product.selected_or_first_available_variant -%}
                    {%- assign sai_eli_img = '' -%}
                    {%- if sai_eli_product.featured_image != blank -%}
                      {%- assign sai_eli_img = sai_eli_product.featured_image | image_url: width: 800 -%}
                    {%- endif -%}
                    {%- unless sai_eli_first -%},{%- endunless -%}
                    {%- assign sai_eli_first = false -%}
                    {
                      "product_id": {{ sai_eli_product.id | json }},
                      "title": {{ sai_eli_product.title | json }},
                      "handle": {{ sai_eli_product.handle | json }},
                      "url": {{ sai_eli_product.url | json }},
                      "image_url": {{ sai_eli_img | json }},
                      "variant_id": {{ sai_eli_variant.id | json }},
                      "available": {{ sai_eli_variant.available | json }},
                      "price": {{ sai_eli_variant.price | money | json }}
                    }
                  {%- endunless -%}
                {%- endif -%}
              {%- endfor -%}
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- endfor -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  ],
  {%- comment -%}
    Grouped editorial looks for the result-step filmstrip: each entry is one
    curated look (its `title` + every outfit product, current product included
    so the tile's product count matches the merchant's look). The flat
    `editorialLooks` above stays as-is for the legacy companion path; `looks`
    is additive. The walk is bounded (≤6 looks, ≤6 products each) to stay within
    Shopify's connected-reference budget, mirroring Shop the Look's access.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  "looks": [
    {%- assign sai_lk_first = true -%}
    {%- assign sai_lk_count = 0 -%}
    {%- if sai_eli_slots -%}
      {%- for sai_slot in sai_eli_slots -%}
        {%- if sai_lk_count >= 6 -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
        {%- if sai_slot.looks.value -%}
          {%- for sai_look in sai_slot.looks.value -%}
            {%- if sai_lk_count >= 6 -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
            {%- if sai_look.outfit.value -%}
              {%- assign sai_lk_count = sai_lk_count | plus: 1 -%}
              {%- unless sai_lk_first -%},{%- endunless -%}
              {%- assign sai_lk_first = false -%}
              {%- comment -%}
                Look hero — the styled photo of the whole outfit (the look's
                first image asset). This is what the filmstrip tile shows: a
                look is a styled combination, not a single garment, so it gets
                its own representative image. The client falls back to a product
                image only when a look has no hero asset.
              {%- endcomment -%}
              {%- assign sai_hero = '' -%}
              {%- if sai_look.assets.value -%}
                {%- for sai_asset in sai_look.assets.value -%}
                  {%- if sai_asset.media.value != blank -%}
                    {%- assign sai_hero = sai_asset.media.value | image_url: width: 800 -%}
                    {%- break -%}
                  {%- endif -%}
                {%- endfor -%}
              {%- endif -%}
              {
                "id": "look-{{ sai_lk_count }}",
                "title": {{ sai_look.title | default: 'Look' | json }},
                "hero_image": {{ sai_hero | json }},
                "products": [
                  {%- assign sai_op_first = true -%}
                  {%- assign sai_op_count = 0 -%}
                  {%- for sai_oe in sai_look.outfit.value -%}
                    {%- if sai_op_count >= 6 -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
                    {%- assign sai_op_product = sai_oe.product.value -%}
                    {%- if sai_op_product -%}
                      {%- assign sai_op_count = sai_op_count | plus: 1 -%}
                      {%- assign sai_op_variant = sai_op_product.selected_or_first_available_variant -%}
                      {%- assign sai_op_img = '' -%}
                      {%- if sai_op_product.featured_image != blank -%}
                        {%- assign sai_op_img = sai_op_product.featured_image | image_url: width: 800 -%}
                      {%- endif -%}
                      {%- assign sai_op_pid = sai_op_product.id | append: '' -%}
                      {%- unless sai_op_first -%},{%- endunless -%}
                      {%- assign sai_op_first = false -%}
                      {
                        "product_id": {{ sai_op_product.id | json }},
                        "title": {{ sai_op_product.title | json }},
                        "handle": {{ sai_op_product.handle | json }},
                        "url": {{ sai_op_product.url | json }},
                        "image_url": {{ sai_op_img | json }},
                        "variant_id": {{ sai_op_variant.id | json }},
                        "available": {{ sai_op_variant.available | json }},
                        "price": {{ sai_op_variant.price | money | json }},
                        "role": {{ sai_oe.role | json }},
                        "is_current": {%- if sai_op_pid == sai_eli_current -%}true{%- else -%}false{%- endif -%},
                        {%- comment -%}
                          Per-product variants so the look panel can offer a size
                          (variant) picker before add-to-cart. Capped at 10 to
                          bound payload size; one-variant products emit a single
                          entry and the client shows no picker.
                        {%- endcomment -%}
                        "variants": [
                          {%- assign sai_op_vfirst = true -%}
                          {%- for sai_op_v in sai_op_product.variants -%}
                            {%- if forloop.index > 10 -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
                            {%- unless sai_op_vfirst -%},{%- endunless -%}
                            {%- assign sai_op_vfirst = false -%}
                            {
                              "id": {{ sai_op_v.id | json }},
                              "title": {{ sai_op_v.title | json }},
                              "available": {{ sai_op_v.available | json }}
                            }
                          {%- endfor -%}
                        ]
                      }
                    {%- endif -%}
                  {%- endfor -%}
                ]
              }
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- endfor -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  ],
  "customerPhoto": {{ customer.metafields.spectrum_customer.vto_photo.value | json }},
  "vtoReferenceImage": {{ product.metafields.spectrum.vto_reference_image.value | json }},
  "family": {{ vto_family | json }},
  "props": {
    "dailyGenerationLimit": {{ content.daily_generation_limit | default: 10 | json }},
    "consentText": {{ content.consent_text | json }},
    "disclaimerText": {{ content.disclaimer_text | json }},
    "showBranding": {{ show_branding | json }}
  }
}
    </script>
  </sai-o1uear1c>

{%- endif -%}
